The paper discusses a machine comprehension algorithm that allows for natural language queries on the content of a document. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The algorithm also uses a neuromodel, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The use of a neuromodel also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with search and retrieval of information, which could potentially fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
